Liveness
--------
Liveness is a process probe sends signal tp that the container or application is either alive(passing) or dead(falling).
If the container is alive,then no action is required. coz current state is good.
If the container is dead, then an attempt should be made to heal to application by restarting it.

In simple words liveness answers a true or false question: "is this container alive?".

Readyness
----------
A readiness probe used to know weather the container or app being probe is ready to start receiving the network traffic.
If container enters a state where it is still alive but cannot handle incoming network traffic ( common scenario during start-up), you want to readiness probe to to fall.

If someone prematurely send network traffic to the container. It could cause load balancer or router to route to return 502 error to the client and terminate the request.
The client would get  a "connection refused " error message.

In simple words, liveness answers a true-or-false question: " is this container ready to take network traffic ?"
